  "text_preview": "\"numbers\" ASL American Sign Language ASL University ► fractions Numbers 1-10 / 11-20 / 21-30 / 31-40 / 100-900 / 1000 and up / Fractions FRACTIONS The idea here is to show two numbers with the top number being the numerator and the bottom number being the denominator. One-half: Here is a more \"casual\" way to sign 1/2 Note: In everyday usage, most fractions are often done while holding the hand palm back with the fingertips pointing somewhat to the left. One-fourth: For all of the various fractions you just show the numerator, then move the hand down a bit and show the denominator. Numbers 1-10 / 11-20 / 21-30 / 31-40 / 100-900 / 1000 and up / Fractions ASL University ► You can learn American Sign Language (ASL) online at American Sign Language University ™ ASL resources by Lifeprint.com © "
}
